Unused terminals:

    COLON

Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> program
Rule 1     program -> statements
Rule 2     statements -> statements statement
Rule 3     statements -> statement
Rule 4     statement -> expression SEMICOLON
Rule 5     statement -> VAR NAME ASSIGN expression SEMICOLON
Rule 6     statement -> NAME ASSIGN expression SEMICOLON
Rule 7     statement -> function_def
Rule 8     statement -> extern_decl
Rule 9     statement -> RETURN expression SEMICOLON
Rule 10    function_def -> FN NAME LPAREN params RPAREN LBRACE statements RBRACE
Rule 11    params -> params COMMA NAME
Rule 12    params -> NAME
Rule 13    params -> <empty>
Rule 14    extern_decl -> EXTERN NAME LPAREN extern_params RPAREN SEMICOLON
Rule 15    extern_params -> extern_params COMMA extern_type
Rule 16    extern_params -> extern_type
Rule 17    extern_params -> <empty>
Rule 18    extern_type -> NAME
Rule 19    expression -> expression PLUS expression
Rule 20    expression -> expression MINUS expression
Rule 21    expression -> expression TIMES expression
Rule 22    expression -> expression DIVIDE expression
Rule 23    expression -> LPAREN expression RPAREN
Rule 24    expression -> PLUS expression
Rule 25    expression -> MINUS expression
Rule 26    expression -> NUMBER
Rule 27    expression -> NAME
Rule 28    expression -> STRING
Rule 29    expression -> function_call
Rule 30    function_call -> NAME LPAREN args RPAREN
Rule 31    args -> args COMMA expression
Rule 32    args -> expression
Rule 33    args -> <empty>

